She describes experiencing physical changes, including significant weight gain, and the onset of agoraphobia, a fear of public spaces. Panettiere shares that the loss has left her heartbroken and unable to reconcile the void, stating that she has "lost half her soul." She discusses the challenging journey of healing in the wake of this tragedy, acknowledging that she will always carry the pain and grief of her brother's absence.

summary: The COVID-19 XEC variant has emerged and is rapidly spreading globally. Experts predict it may become the dominant strain. The variant has been detected in multiple countries, including the UK, Europe, and the United States. Health officials emphasize the importance of staying up-to-date with vaccinations and taking precautions such as mask-wearing and social distancing to mitigate the spread of the virus.
